It's possible that the issue lies with the definition of `y`, rather than the optimization function.

The values of `alpha` and `k` determine the shape of the Pareto distribution, so they might affect the results of the optimization. I would recommend trying different values of `alpha` and `k` to see if it changes the outcome. If you still experience the same error, you might need to double-check the code and see if there are any other issues.
